Commentary

This is where Jung becomes alchemical. The third thing is not a compromise. It is not half-conscious and half-unconscious. It is a new symbolic position that could not have been reached by either side alone.

For practice, this means the image should not be solved too quickly. If an inner figure appears as hostile, seductive, frightened, radiant, animal, angelic, or grotesque, the task is not immediate interpretation. The task is contact. What does it want? What does it know? What does it accuse? What does it carry that consciousness excluded?

The symbol is born only if the tension is endured.

