This is the crucial safeguard. Jung does not allow the imaginal to become escape. The fantasy has meaning only if the person pays tribute to life. The inner image must change outer conduct, otherwise it remains sterile.

This makes active imagination a discipline of incarnation. One receives the image, dialogues with it, gives it form, and then asks what demand it makes upon life. A symbol that never returns to action becomes theatre. A symbol that reorders action becomes transformation.

The transcendent function is therefore not a doorway out of the world. It is the bridge by which the hidden psyche returns to the world with a new form of life.

