Commentary

This is the central Blakean practice. Nothing needs to be added to reality. The doors must be cleansed. The world appears finite because the human being has closed himself up.

This is an imaginal doctrine of perception. The infinite is not elsewhere. It is hidden by contraction. The cavern is not the world, but the condition of seeing. The practice is therefore not escape but purification of vision.

Blake’s fire is not annihilation of the world. It is annihilation of the crust over the world.

