Heaven as a State of the Soul — Swedenborg and Spiritual Space

Commentary

Swedenborg gives one of the clearest pre-Corbin descriptions of visionary geography. Heaven is not a vague abstraction, nor merely a reward after death. It has societies, directions, houses, garments, speech, light, heat, appearances, and distances. But these are not physical in the ordinary sense. They correspond to inner states.

This is why Corbin recognised Swedenborg as a Western witness to the imaginal world. Space in heaven is real, but it is not measured by miles. It is measured by love, wisdom, affinity, and state.

