The Heavenly City

Commentary

A city of states rather than a city of measurable distances.

Commentary

The sequence matters. Swedenborg places space after state and time. This means spiritual geography cannot be understood by ordinary location first. One must understand the life of angels: their love, wisdom, alternation, perception, and interior form.

Only then can one understand heavenly space. Place is not primary. State is primary. Space appears as the outer form of state.

This gives a precise imaginal rule: the inner becomes spatial. A society of love appears as a dwelling. Wisdom appears as light. Affinity appears as nearness. Difference appears as distance.

