Morning in Heaven

Commentary

Light and warmth as appearances of love and wisdom.

Commentary

Swedenborg’s heaven is dynamic. Angels do not remain in one static brightness. Their states change like morning, noon, evening, shade, warmth, and cold. But these are not merely atmospheric conditions. They are outward appearances of inward life.

This is imaginal meteorology. Weather becomes soul. Light becomes wisdom. Heat becomes love. Dawn becomes renewal. Evening becomes obscuration. The world is read as correspondence.

For practice, this teaches the reader to notice inner weather. A mood is not just a mood. It may have light, temperature, direction, landscape. The imaginal eye reads the state as a world.

