Commentary

Time becoming state in the spiritual world.

Commentary

This is one of Swedenborg’s most radical claims. There is succession in heaven, but not time as we know it. Angels do not organise reality through hours, days, and years. They perceive progression as state.

This transforms spiritual practice. The question is not only “what time is it?” but “what state am I in?” A single hour can contain a descent, dawn, distance, nearness, exile, return. The soul’s clock is qualitative.

The imaginal realm does not abolish sequence. It transfigures sequence into meaning.

