Commentary

This is where Swedenborg most clearly enters the imaginal. Heaven is not a blank abstraction. Angels see objects. They dwell in places. They speak. They perceive forms more vivid than earthly forms.

But the essence of these objects differs from earthly objects. They arise from the sun of heaven, from love and wisdom, from interiors expressing themselves outwardly. Everything visible is correspondence.

This is the world Corbin needs: a real world of images that is neither crude matter nor private fantasy.

