Steiner's progression is striking because he refuses to let imagination become the final goal. Living pictures eventually become transparent. One no longer attends only to what appears, but begins listening for what speaks through appearance.

This transforms symbols from static objects into expressions of living beings. Images become language. Forms become communication. The imaginal world becomes conversational rather than merely visual.

