The Stranger Meets the Guide

Commentary

A solitary traveller encountering the luminous guide at the beginning of the inward journey.

The Guide appears before any doctrine is explained. Corbin insists this order is deliberate. The soul does not begin with concepts. It begins with encounter.

The Guide is not merely another character within the story. He represents the emergence of a higher mode of knowing that arrives as a person before it becomes an idea. Throughout Islamic visionary literature, wisdom repeatedly appears with a face.

