The Ladder of Interpretation

Commentary

A symbolic ascent in which every image leads beyond itself.

For Corbin, interpretation is never the replacement of image with concept.

The image is not discarded once its meaning is known. Rather, the image becomes increasingly transparent, allowing the soul to pass through it toward the reality that first generated it. Every authentic symbol therefore remains alive. It cannot be exhausted by explanation.

This is why visionary literature demands contemplation more than decoding.

