Commentary

The rising light representing the homeland from which consciousness descends.

One of Corbin's greatest recoveries is the original meaning of "Orient."

It is not a direction on a compass.

The Orient is the place where light rises within being itself. The visionary journey therefore proceeds neither east nor west geographically. It moves toward the soul's own dawn. Spiritual geography replaces terrestrial geography.

