The Personal Angel

Commentary

An angel standing as the higher individuality toward which the soul is gradually becoming.

Corbin's angelology is profoundly different from popular religious imagery.

The angel is not merely a supernatural messenger visiting from elsewhere. The angel is simultaneously guide, heavenly archetype, and future self. Individuation occurs through fidelity to this relationship.

This explains why visionary encounters possess such transformative force. The soul is not meeting an abstraction. It is meeting the image of its own completed reality.

