The Returning Bird

Commentary

The bird rising beyond the visible horizon toward its forgotten homeland.

The recurring image of the bird gathers together everything that has come before.

The Guide has shown the way. The symbols have become transparent. The Orient has been remembered. The angel has revealed the soul's true direction.

Flight is therefore not escape from the world.

It is the recovery of the world's hidden depth. The visionary recital concludes not by rejecting embodiment, but by revealing that every genuine journey through the imaginal is also a return toward one's own celestial origin.

